                     <p>
                        <pb n="389"/> Indenture dated 24 March, 1 Q. Mary, by which 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Foster</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108454">Evelyn, in the county of Salop</placeName>, esq.</persName>, 
               demises to farm to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Gardner</surname>
                        </persName>, 
               <persName nymRef="Gardner">
                           <forename>Margaret</forename> his wife</persName>,
               and <persName nymRef="Gardner">
                           <forename>George</forename> his son</persName>, one messuage and plough-land, with 
               half the heath called the 'Haule heathe,' lying in <placeName key="place_108475">Hynynton</placeName> in the said county, for
               the term of their lives; paying annually 26s. 8d. 
               . </p>
